cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with computer vision and robotics, specifically scale estimation for monocular SfM in a multi-modal stereo camera system. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.RO (Robotics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves multi-modal imaging, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). The proposed method uses batch optimization, which is a common technique in machine learning and optimization, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves numerical stability, which is a common concern in machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category as well.
